285 g Top Sirloin Steak
100 g Bacon Strips
2 unit(s) Egg
113 g Mushrooms
3 unit(s) Russet Potato
4 tbsp Maple Syrup
1 unit(s) Beef Broth Concentrate
20 g Gravy Spice Blend
4 g Garlic Salt
1 unit(s) Shallot
7 g Chives
7.5 g Beef Stock Powder
2.5 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, preheat the oven to 450°F.
Wash and dry all produce.
Remove any brown spots from potatoes, then cut into 1/2-inch wedges.
To a parchment-lined baking sheet, add potatoes, 1/2 tsp (1 tsp) garlic salt and 1 tbsp oil. (NOTE: For 4 servings, use 2 baking sheets, with 1 tbsp oil per sheet.) Season with pepper, then toss to coat.

Roast potatoes in the middle of the oven for 25-28 min, flipping halfway through, until tender and golden. (NOTE: For 4 servings, roast in the middle and bottom of the oven, rotating sheets halfway through.)

Meanwhile, thinly slice mushroooms.
Peel, then cut shallot into 1/4-inch slices.
Thinly slice chives.
Cut bacon into 1/2-inch pieces.
Pat steaks dry with paper towels. Season with 1/2 tsp (1 tsp) garlic salt and pepper.
Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high. When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then steaks. Cook 1-2 per side, until browned.

Remove from heat and transfer steaks to an unlined baking sheet.
Roast in the top of the oven 5-8 min, or until cooked to desired doneness.**
When steaks are done, remove from heat and transfer to a plate. Loosely cover with foil and set aside to rest for 2-3 min.
Carefully, wipe the pan clean.
Add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil to the same pan. Crack in eggs. Season with salt and pepper. Pan-fry 2-3 min, covered, until egg whites are set. (NOTE: Yolks will still be runny!)
Transfer to a plate and cover to keep warm.

Meanwhile, add bacon to the same pan. (NOTE: For 4 servings, cook bacon in batches.) Cook for 5-8 min, flipping occasionally, until crispy.** Remove with a slotted spoon to a paper towel-lined plate.
Remove all but 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) bacon fat from the pan, then add mushrooms and shallots. Cook 2-3 min, stirring occasionally, until softened. Season with salt and pepper.
Reduce heat to medium. Add Gravy Spice Blend. Cook 1-2 min, stirring often, until fragrant.
Add 1/2 cup (1 cup) water, broth concentrate, stock powder and half the maple syrup. Bring to a boil over high, then reduce heat to medium. Cook 2-4 min, until slightly thickened.
Remove the pan from heat.

Thinly slice steaks. Stir steak resting juices into the gravy.
Divide potatoes between plates, then top with steak.
Top steak with maple-mushroom gravy, then sprinkle with bacon.
Top with eggs.
Sprinkle chives over top, then drizzle with as much of the remaining maple syrup as desired.